cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.AR 

This paper presents techniques for reducing the computational cost of classifiers based on learned transforms and soft-thresholding. These techniques are relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and robotics (cs.AR). However, given the focus on classification and optimization, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories.
